[PROFILE] Completed with 3 findings:
  > Rationale: Olo is a highly established, reputable enterprise restaurant technology provider. Founded 20 years ago (originally as GoMobo), it operates a transactional SaaS business model that digitizes online ordering, delivery management, and payment processing for major fast-food and restaurant chains. The company serves over 90,000 locations across 800+ top restaurant brands (such as Chipotle, Texas Roadhouse, and Panda Express). Its core product suites include Order (direct-to-consumer digital ordering), Rails (menu synchronization to third-party marketplaces), Dispatch (delivery management), and Olo Pay (payment processing). The company's operational profile is highly robust, with strong enterprise market penetration, high switching costs, and a clear, validated business model. There are no operational discrepancies or red flags indicating a shell company or fake operations.
  - [INFO] Olo is a highly established enterprise restaurant technology provider powering digital ordering, delivery, and payments for over 90,000 locations and 800+ major brands.
  - [INFO] The company operates a robust transactional SaaS business model consisting of three core suites: Order (direct digital ordering), Rails (marketplace integration), and Dispatch (delivery orchestration), supplemented by Olo Pay and Engage (guest data platform).
  - [INFO] Olo is expanding its digital footprint into physical, card-present transactions (via self-service kiosks and POS integrations like NCR Voyix and FreedomPay) to capture non-digital restaurant sales.
